{"id":"hep-th/9201002","submitter":null,"authors":"F.Bonechi, E.Celeghini, R.Giachetti, E.Sorace and M.Tarlini","title":"Inomogeneous Quantum Groups as Symmetries of Phonons","comments":"5 pags. 0 figs","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.Lett. 68 (1992) 3718-3720","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.68.3718","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  The quantum deformed (1+1) Poincare' algebra is shown to be the kinematical\nsymmetry of the harmonic chain, whose spacing is given by the deformation\nparameter. Phonons with their symmetries as well as multiphonon processes are\nderived from the quantum group structure. Inhomogeneous quantum groups are thus\nproposed as kinematical invariance of discrete systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Jan 1992 12:17:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-22"}
